Pre-Game Insights: The Confederation of African Football (CAF) has appointed four Ugandan officials to handle the FIFA World Cup qualifier preliminary round group A game between Djibouti and Ethiopia.
Ali Sabilla Chelengat will be the center referee for the contest slated for 9th June, 2024 at El Jadida Stadium in Morocco.
He will be assisted by Ronald Katenya and Hakim Mulindwa as the first and second assistants while William Oloya will be the fourth official.
Nigeria’s Shantal Shuaibu Amiru is the referee assessor while Mohamed Khalid Abdallah from Tanzania is the match commissioner.
